Durban - IFP leader Mangosuthu Buthelezi's son Prince Ntuthukoyezwe Zuzifa Buthelezi on Friday paid tribute his father's remarkable resilience. Buthelezi celebrated his 90th birthday with a gala dinner at Durban's ICC. Guests included former presidents Jacob Zuma and FW de Klerk, former first ladies Graca Machel and Zanele Mbeki, Colonel Panji Kaunda the son of former Zambian president Kenneth Kaunda, KZN Premier Willies Mchunu, Minister of Energy Jeff Radebe, Cogta Minister Zweli Mkhize, DA leader Mmusi Maimane, Princess Zenani Dlamini-Mandela and Nicky and Orcillia Oppenheimer. Entertainment was provided by the KZN philharmonic orchestra and musician Natalie Rungan with renowned author Gcina Mhlophe. Zuzifa said the family wanted to celebrate his father's legacy while he was alive. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
